(1009,63,'service_faqs_1_question','Why is my heater blowing cold air?'),
(1010,63,'_service_faqs_1_question','field_faq_question'),
(1011,63,'service_faqs_1_answer','Common causes include thermostat set incorrectly (on \"cool\" or \"fan only\"), heat pump reversing valve stuck in cooling mode, defrost cycle running (heat pumps), pilot light or ignition failure (furnaces), low refrigerant in heat pumps, or emergency heat strips failed. We diagnose the exact cause and provide cost-effective repair solutions.'),
(1012,63,'_service_faqs_1_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1013,63,'service_faqs_2_question','How much does heating repair cost?'),
(1014,63,'_service_faqs_2_question','field_faq_question'),
(1015,63,'service_faqs_2_answer','Heating repair costs vary by problem. Simple fixes like thermostat replacement ($150-$300) or ignitor replacement ($200-$400) are affordable. Major repairs like reversing valve replacement ($800-$1,500) or heat exchanger replacement ($1,000-$2,000) cost more. We always provide upfront pricing before starting work.'),
(1016,63,'_service_faqs_2_answer','field_faq_answer'),
