(1383,68,'service_faqs_0_answer','A ductless mini-split is an HVAC system with an outdoor compressor unit connected to one or more indoor air handlers without ductwork. Small refrigerant lines run through a 3-inch hole in the wall. Each indoor unit cools (and heats) independently, giving you precise room-by-room temperature control. They\'re ideal for homes without ducts or room additions.'),
