(1389,68,'service_faqs_2_question','Are ductless mini-splits more efficient than central AC?'),
(1390,68,'_service_faqs_2_question','field_faq_question'),
(1391,68,'service_faqs_2_answer','Yes! Ductless mini-splits achieve 18-30+ SEER efficiency versus 14-18 SEER for most central AC systems. They avoid the 20-30% energy loss from leaky ductwork. Zoning capability means you only cool rooms you\'re using. Most homeowners save 30-50% on cooling costs compared to traditional AC or window units.'),
(1392,68,'_service_faqs_2_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1393,68,'service_faqs_3_question','Can ductless mini-splits heat and cool?'),
(1394,68,'_service_faqs_3_question','field_faq_question'),
(1395,68,'service_faqs_3_answer','Yes! Most ductless mini-splits are heat pumps that provide both cooling and heating. They\'re extremely efficient for heating in South Florida\'s mild winters (more efficient than electric heat). This makes them perfect year-round comfort solutions requiring just one system instead of separate AC and heat.'),
(1396,68,'_service_faqs_3_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1397,68,'service_faqs_4_question','How many rooms can one outdoor unit handle?'),
(1398,68,'_service_faqs_4_question','field_faq_question'),
(1399,68,'service_faqs_4_answer','Multi-zone outdoor units can connect to 2-8 indoor units (zones) depending on the model. Each zone operates independently with its own temperature control. This is perfect for cooling multiple bedrooms, a home addition, or specific rooms without cooling your entire house.'),
(1400,68,'_service_faqs_4_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1401,68,'service_faqs_5_question','Are ductless systems noisy?'),
(1402,68,'_service_faqs_5_question','field_faq_question'),
