(1778,167,'service_faqs_0_question','How often should I schedule AC maintenance?'),
(1779,167,'_service_faqs_0_question','field_faq_question'),
(1780,167,'service_faqs_0_answer','We recommend professional AC maintenance twice per yearonce in spring before summer heat and once in fall. In South Florida\'s demanding climate where AC systems run nearly year-round, semi-annual maintenance ensures peak performance and catches issues early.'),
(1781,167,'_service_faqs_0_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1782,167,'service_faqs_1_question','What\'s included in an AC maintenance visit?'),
(1783,167,'_service_faqs_1_question','field_faq_question'),
(1784,167,'service_faqs_1_answer','Our comprehensive service includes a 20-point inspection, filter replacement or cleaning, coil cleaning, refrigerant level check, electrical connection inspection and tightening, condensate drain clearing, thermostat calibration, lubrication of moving parts, airflow measurement, and performance testing.'),
(1785,167,'_service_faqs_1_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1786,167,'service_faqs_2_question','How much does AC maintenance cost?'),
(1787,167,'_service_faqs_2_question','field_faq_question'),
(1788,167,'service_faqs_2_answer','Maintenance visits typically range from $79-$150 depending on system size and complexity. However, maintenance saves far more than it costs by preventing expensive repairs, reducing energy bills by 15-20%, and extending equipment life by years. Ask about our maintenance membership plans for additional savings.'),
(1789,167,'_service_faqs_2_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1790,167,'service_faqs_3_question','Can I skip maintenance if my AC seems to be working fine?'),
(1791,167,'_service_faqs_3_question','field_faq_question'),
(1792,167,'service_faqs_3_answer','Noregular maintenance is essential even when your AC appears to work properly. Many problems develop gradually without obvious symptoms until they cause major failures. Maintenance catches these issues early, maintains efficiency, and is required to keep manufacturer warranties valid.'),
(1793,167,'_service_faqs_3_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1794,167,'service_faqs_4_question','What happens if you find problems during maintenance?'),
(1795,167,'_service_faqs_4_question','field_faq_question'),
(1796,167,'service_faqs_4_answer','If we discover any issues during your maintenance visit, we\'ll explain the problem, show you the affected components, discuss repair options and costs, and provide honest recommendations. You\'ll never be surprised by unexpected chargesall repairs require your approval before we proceed.'),
(1797,167,'_service_faqs_4_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1798,167,'service_faqs_5_question','Does maintenance really prevent breakdowns?'),
(1799,167,'_service_faqs_5_question','field_faq_question'),
(1800,167,'service_faqs_5_answer','Yesstudies show that regular maintenance reduces breakdown risk by up to 95%. Most AC failures result from neglected maintenance issues like dirty coils, low refrigerant, worn belts, or loose electrical connections. Catching and fixing these during routine maintenance prevents costly emergency repairs.'),
(1801,167,'_service_faqs_5_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1802,167,'service_faqs_6_question','Will maintenance lower my energy bills?'),
(1803,167,'_service_faqs_6_question','field_faq_question'),
(1804,167,'service_faqs_6_answer','Absolutely. A well-maintained AC system operates 15-20% more efficiently than a neglected one. Clean coils transfer heat better, proper refrigerant charge optimizes performance, clean filters improve airflow, and tuned components work less hard to cool your homeall resulting in lower monthly energy costs.'),
(1805,167,'_service_faqs_6_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1806,167,'service_faqs_7_question','Do I need maintenance for a new AC system?'),
(1807,167,'_service_faqs_7_question','field_faq_question'),
(1808,167,'service_faqs_7_answer','Yeseven new systems require regular maintenance to maintain peak efficiency and keep warranties valid. Most manufacturers require proof of annual professional maintenance to honor warranty claims. Starting maintenance from day one ensures your new system delivers maximum performance and lifespan.'),
(1809,167,'_service_faqs_7_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1810,167,'service_faqs_8_question','What\'s the difference between maintenance and a tune-up?'),
(1811,167,'_service_faqs_8_question','field_faq_question'),
(1812,167,'service_faqs_8_answer','These terms are often used interchangeably. Both refer to comprehensive preventative service including inspection, cleaning, testing, and adjustment of all system components. Our maintenance service is a complete tune-up designed to optimize performance and prevent problems.'),
(1813,167,'_service_faqs_8_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1814,167,'service_faqs_9_question','Can I perform AC maintenance myself?'),
(1815,167,'_service_faqs_9_question','field_faq_question'),
(1816,167,'service_faqs_9_answer','While you can handle basic tasks like changing filters and keeping outdoor units clear, professional maintenance requires specialized tools, refrigerant handling certification, electrical expertise, and diagnostic equipment. DIY maintenance can\'t replicate the thoroughness of professional service and may void warranties.'),
